gomodel:SYNGO_2653  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.3: \"Spontaneous mossy fiber-granule cell EPSCs\"\n- \"The current-voltage plots of the magnitude of the fast component (peak amplitude of the fast component) were linear in all four genotypes, consistent with the properties of non-NMDA receptor responses. In contrast, the amplitude of the slow component (10 msec after the peak of the fast component) was reduced at hyperpolarized potentials in both the wild-type and NR2A-/- mutant mice (Fig. 3 B). This reduction was more marked in the NR2C-/- mutant mice, and the slow component nearly disappeared in the NR2A-/-/NR2C-/- mutant mice (Fig.3 B). \"\n\nFig.4: \"Granule cell EPSCs elicited by mossy fiber stimulation\"\n- \"The decay time, however, was slightly slower in the NR2A-/- mutant mice than in the wild-type mice and was faster in the NR2C-/- mutant mice (Table 1)\"\n\nAbstract: \"The NR2A and NR2C subunits thus contribute to distinct NMDA receptor-mediated excitatory transmission in mossy fiber-granule cell synapses in the mature cerebellum\". Experimental description: \"Generation of NR2A- and/or NR2C-deficient mice\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2018-02-20" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_2653" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .
